4513	APW_ENG_20020411.0630.LDC2007T07	A leading human rights activist denied in court Thursday that she advocated a separate Kurdish state when she used the word ``Kurdistan'' during a speech at a women's rights conference.
4514	APW_ENG_20020411.0630.LDC2007T07	Eren Keskin, a lawyer and the head of the independent Human Rights Association, faces up to three years in prison if found guilty of charges of separatist propaganda for saying that ``women in Kurdistan face harassment and rape the most'' during a speech she gave in November 2001.
4515	APW_ENG_20020411.0630.LDC2007T07	Keskin, who defended herself in the opening hearing of her trial Thursday, said she had used the word ``Kurdistan'' to describe a geographic region and not to refer to a state separate from Turkey.
