4520	APW_ENG_20020411.0630.LDC2007T07	Turkey fought a 15-year war against Kurdish rebels demanding autonomy in the southeast and is sensitive toward the use of the word ``Kurdistan'' in describing Turkey's mainly Kurdish southeast region.
