5330	APW_ENG_20070115.1140.LDC2009T13	Kosovo's majority ethnic-Albanian population wants independence, but Belgrade has vowed never to agree to that.
5331	APW_ENG_20070115.1140.LDC2009T13	A Kremlin statement said that during a Serbian-initiated telephone conversation, Putin "affirmed Russia's fundamental position" on the issue of Kosovo -- that any solution must be acceptable to Serbia.
5332	APW_ENG_20070115.1140.LDC2009T13	Ahtisaari's widely anticipated but as yet unannounced proposal would need U.N. Security Council approval before becoming an internationally accepted solution for the troubled province, which has been an international protectorate since 1999.
5333	APW_ENG_20070115.1140.LDC2009T13	"Putin has stressed that a (Kosovo) solution must be derived ... from the principles of territorial integrity and sovereignty of existing countries," Kostunica told reporters, reiterating that Serbia would lose 15 percent of its territory if Kosovo breaks away.
5334	APW_ENG_20070115.1140.LDC2009T13	Formally still part of Serbia, Kosovo has been run by a U.N. mission and NATO troops since the 1998-1999 war there between Serbian troops and the separatists.
5335	APW_ENG_20070115.1140.LDC2009T13	The fighting ended when NATO bombed Serbs and forced them to pull out of Kosovo.
5336	APW_ENG_20070115.1140.LDC2009T13	Moscow has not specified what solution for Kosovo it would like to see, but Kostunica said Putin believes anything without consent from both sides would "lead to unnecessary conflicts."
5337	APW_ENG_20070115.1140.LDC2009T13	Russia also suggested that a status decision should not be rushed and that Kosovo's leadership must do more to protect the rights of the Serb minority in Kosovo and enable the return of Serb refugees.
5338	APW_ENG_20070115.1140.LDC2009T13	A spokeswoman for Kosovo's predominantly ethnic Albanian government, Ulpiana Lama, suggested that Kosovo should not be regarded as Serbian territory.
5339	APW_ENG_20070115.1140.LDC2009T13	"We want to assure all sides concerned that Kosovo will respect Serbia's integrity and not make territorial claims over the Presevo Valley," she said.
5340	APW_ENG_20070115.1140.LDC2009T13	The valley is another, adjacent territory with a sizable ethnic Albanian community, but deeper in Serbia proper.
5341	APW_ENG_20070115.1140.LDC2009T13	Kostunica thanked Putin profusely for the support, adding that "Putin's word ... has brought about a turnaround" in debates on Kosovo's future.
5342	APW_ENG_20070115.1140.LDC2009T13	The United States has repeatedly signaled to Serbia that it should drop its opposition to an independent Kosovo.
