5826	APW_ENG_20070202.1273.LDC2009T13	Democrats energized by their takeover of Congress began a campaign to do the same with the U.S. presidency on Friday in the first public gathering of all the party's White House hopefuls.
5827	APW_ENG_20070202.1273.LDC2009T13	Sen. Barack Obama began his speech to members of the Democratic National Committee with a joke about how the contest feels a little like "American Idol" or "Survivor" reality shows.
5828	APW_ENG_20070202.1273.LDC2009T13	But he quickly tried to tap into what he said is a sober mood in the United States weighed down by the Iraq war and concerns about health care and pensions.
5829	APW_ENG_20070202.1273.LDC2009T13	He spoke softly and carried the crowd with his call for an honest debate on the issues.
5830	APW_ENG_20070202.1273.LDC2009T13	"Democrats, this is not a game," Obama said.
5831	APW_ENG_20070202.1273.LDC2009T13	"This can't be about who digs up more skeletons on who, who makes the biggest slip-ups on the campaign trail.
5832	APW_ENG_20070202.1273.LDC2009T13	We owe it to the American people to do more than that.
5833	APW_ENG_20070202.1273.LDC2009T13	We owe them an election where voters are inspired."
