5893	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	Radio songs a gauge of Gaza ' s fighting
5894	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	looters are the clear winners of the war
5895	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	2007-02-05 17:55:56 UTC
5896	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	EDITORS' NOTE: AP reporter Sarah El Deeb has been covering Gaza's factional fighting, often pinned down indoors by gunfire and venturing outside during periods of lull.
5897	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	Here are her notes from the sidelines
5898	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	By SARAH EL DEEB
5899	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	Associated Press Writer
5900	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	GAZA CITY, Gaza Strip (AP) -- Never mind the almost daily cease- fire announcements.
5901	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	The music played on the radio stations of Hamas and Fatah is a much better guide to war and peace.
5902	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	When both Hamas's Al Aqsa radio and Fatah's Al Shabab station played "Today is the day of rage" simultaneously a few days ago, it was pretty clear the guns would not fall silent.
5903	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	At times of heavy clashes, the playlists also include Islamic marching songs or odes to legendary Fatah founder Yasser Arafat.
5904	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	When the two sides withdraw their forces from time to time, songs about Jerusalem are popular, as a unifying theme.
5905	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	Lebanese singer Fairouz is a favorite on Al Shabab, as a demonstration of secular nationalist sentiment.
5906	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	Radio broadcasts also air political statements and take calls from listeners trapped at home.
5907	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	Trying to lower the enemy's morale, Al Shabab reported that scores of Hamas militiamen had defected.
5908	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	Al Aqsa Radio quickly retaliated with a similar report.
5909	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	When a new cease-fire was announced Sunday, both stations broadcast the same phone number for listeners to report violations to a police operations room with Hamas and Fatah observers.
5910	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	They received dozens of calls on the first day.
5911	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	And resumed playing songs of national unity.
5912	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	---
5913	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	After nightfall, thunderous gunfire frequently erupted outside a building housing visiting Associated Press staffers in Gaza City, with some of the shooting coming from a nearby building.
5914	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	It was more than just a fight between Hamas and Fatah.
5915	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	The Bakr clan, clamoring for revenge, was after the killer of a 17-year-old member, Mahmoud Bakr, who died in the crossfire last week.
5916	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	For four nights, dozens of masked Bakr men, armed and in black uniforms, pinned down a dozen Hamas gunmen -- whom they blamed for Mahmoud's death -- on a rooftop.
5917	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	The fighting is increasingly about settling personal scores, and the element of revenge will make it harder to enforce a cease- fire, even if Hamas and Fatah are to reach an elusive power- sharing agreement.
5918	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	The grieving father, Anan Bakr, a member of the Fatah-linked Preventive Security Service, said the battle has become personal.
5919	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	"In our tradition, in our religion, whoever kills must be killed, even after time passes," he said.
5920	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	---
5921	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	An 11-year-old boy looting floor tiles from a ransacked Preventive Security Service compound in the northern town of Beit Lahiya is one of the few clear winners in the factional fighting.
5922	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	The boy, who wouldn't give his name because he is stealing government property, is selling the tiles for 1.50 shekels ($0.45, 35 European cents) a piece and has also ripped 12 window frames out of the now unguarded complex, attacked by Hamas over the weekend.
5923	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	Hamas and Fatah have fought each other to a draw after several weeks of fighting -- though the Fatah-allied security forces took a bad hit in the last four-day round that ended Sunday.
5924	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	Twenty members of the Fatah-allied security forces were killed, compared to four from Hamas and seven civilians.
5925	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	---
5926	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	Abdel Nasser Hamad had kept his supermarket in the beachside Rimal neighborhood open throughout the fighting, with shutters half closed to protect his front window against stray bullets.
5927	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	For four days, he had no customers.
5928	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	On Sunday, the first day of a new lull, business was still slow.
5929	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	AP reporters made his day with a 300 shekel ($70, or euro54) purchase of coffee, tea, crackers and other staples
5930	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	our supplies had run low after being confined to an apartment for four days.
5931	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	Outside Hamad's store, we loaded the bags into an armored car and drove back to the apartment.
5932	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	At one junction, gunmen ordered us to stop and searched the car, apparently suspicious that we were transporting weapons.
5933	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	The groceries passed the test and we were allowed to move on.
5934	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	---
5935	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	The middle ground is not a popular place in Gaza these days.
5936	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	On Sunday, various groups trying to stop the fighting, including a small Palestine Liberation Organization faction and several NGOs, set up an open-sided tent near the parliament building and asked passers-by to join a protest vigil.
5937	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	About 700 people showed up, sitting under the tarp, shaking hands and smoking with organizers from the "Bridge of Love" group.
5938	APW_ENG_20070205.1093.LDC2009T13	Hamas and Fatah can each mobilize thousands for their rallies.
