7099	APW_ENG_20070418.1355.LDC2009T13	A freelance journalist who said she left New York's "rat race" for the adventure of the Peace Corps was found dead Wednesday, her body in a shallow grave in the northern Philippines where she had gone to hike, officials said.
7100	APW_ENG_20070418.1355.LDC2009T13	Police said they believed foul play was involved in the death of Julia Campbell, 40, from Fairfax, Virginia, who came to the country two years ago and had about two weeks left in an English- teaching stint.
