7149	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	Tribeca festival presents a diverse lineup for a myriad of moviegoers
7150	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	NEW YORK 2007-04-23 18:02:53 UTC
7151	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	The word "tentpole" is used to describe a blockbuster movie that can appeal to everyone.
7152	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	If it were applied to a festival, the Tribeca Film Festival would be it.
7153	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	The sixth annual festival opens Wednesday with a wide selection of international art house fare, populist premieres and family friendly films -- 157 features and 88 shorts jammed into 12 days of screenings, panel discussions and parties.
7154	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	Since being founded in response to the Sept. 11 attacks by Robert De Niro, his producing partner, Jane Rosenthal, and her husband, the entrepreneur Craig Hatkoff, the Tribeca festival has gradually developed an identity as diverse as the city itself.
7155	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	"We're showing everything from an avant garde film called `Passio' with live music by Arvo Part at the Cathedral of St. John the Divine -- to `Spider-Man 3,'" said chief festival programmer and executive director Peter Scarlet.
7156	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	"You can't get two things that are more unlike each other, but it's that almost surreal juxtaposition of different kinds of things that I think is an example of how we're trying to redefine what a film festival is."
7157	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	Tribeca was launched in 2002, as Rosenthal says, because of an "act of war."
7158	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	She and De Niro wanted to do something to benefit their neighborhood, just north of where the World Trade Center towers once stood.
7159	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	They began with no long-term plans, but six years later, the festival has become an international fixture -- nestled between the more domestic Sundance Film Festival in January and the pre- eminent international fest, Cannes, in mid-May.
7160	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	Because of its origins, Tribeca will always be defined by its connection to Sept. 11 and the continuing reverberations of that tragedy.
7161	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	"We are a political festival," said Rosenthal in a recent interview in her Tribeca office.
7162	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	Though Tribeca in its early years intentionally opened with heartwarming comedies like "About a Boy," last year it confronted its history by opening with "United 93," the documentary-like recounting of the flight that crashed in Pennsylvania on Sept. 11.
7163	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	The festival has increasingly highlighted films that deal with post-Sept.11 issues like the Iraq and Afghanistan wars.
7164	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	That mission expands this year with a series of global warming-themed short films produced by the SOS (Save Our Selves) campaign.
7165	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	They will open the festival in a gala hosted by Al Gore on Wednesday.
7166	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	"We will do things and show things and whether you like it or not, it's something to see and it's ways to ask questions," said Rosenthal.
7167	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	"We might be able to do something about climate change quicker than we can do something about our current administration."
7168	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	Among this year's political documentaries are "Taxi to the Dark Side" by Alex Gibney ("Enron: The Smartest Guys in the Room"), which details the policies behind the Abu Ghraib scandal
7169	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	"Beyond Belief," about two Sept. 11 widows traveling to Afghanistan
7170	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	and "I Am an American Soldier: One Year in Iraq in the 101st Airborne," for which filmmaker John Laurence documented soldiers' lives for 14 months.
7171	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	Among the big-tent events are the U.S. premiere of "Spider-Man 3" on April 30
7172	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	the premiere of Curtis Hanson's romance "Lucky You," starring Eric Bana and Drew Barrymore
7173	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	and one of the festival's signature events: the Tribeca Drive-in.
7174	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	"It's really a sit-in," joked Rosenthal, explaining that the outdoor screenings are her favorite part of the festival.
7175	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	This year will feature a 20th anniversary screening of "Dirty Dancing," the animated "Surf's Up" and "Planet B-Boy," a documentary about breakdancing.
7176	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	A new addition this year also pays respect to a genre often given scant attention at movie festivals: the sports movie.
7177	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	Sponsored by ESPN, Tribeca will present 14 premieres of sports-related films, as well as a screening of the baseball classic "The Natural."
7178	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	Serving as ambassadors of the sports festival are former National Foortball League running back and now TV personality Tiki Barber, and tennis legend Billie Jean King.
7179	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	Movies playing in the Tribeca Family Festival include "Gumby: The Movie" and a documentary on student council races in four different middle schools entitled "The Third Monday in October."
7180	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	A festival's merit is often measured in its ability to present movies appealing to distributors -- it is a marketplace.
7181	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	The two most successful Tribeca-showcased films are "Transamerica," which went on to yield Felicity Huffman a best actress Academy Award nomination, and "Jesus Camp," which received an Oscar nomination this year for best documentary.
7182	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	"I'd like to see a narrative picture break out in a mainstream way, but that takes time," said Rosenthal.
7183	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	"You can't do anything about it."
7184	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	Predicting what will catch on this year is impossible, but among the eagerly awaited films are the Leonardo DiCaprio-produced "Gardener of Eden"
7185	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	the poker mockumentary "The Grand"
7186	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	and "Lady Chatterley," an adaptation of the second version (of three) of D.H. Lawrence's erotic novel.
7187	APW_ENG_20070423.1050.LDC2009T13	The film won five Cesar Awards, the French equivalent of the Oscars.
