7718	APW_ENG_20070614.1533.LDC2009T13	PARIS 2007-06-14 19:52:22 UTC
7719	APW_ENG_20070614.1533.LDC2009T13	A series of problems with radiation machines used to treat brain cancer sufferers -- with malfunctioning machines and some patients receiving overdoses -- is raising questions around France about the safety of the treatment.
7720	APW_ENG_20070614.1533.LDC2009T13	The Health Ministry this week ordered half the country's brain tumor radiotherapy machines suspended indefinitely following a warning from the manufacturer, Brainlab, that they were not targeting properly.
7721	APW_ENG_20070614.1533.LDC2009T13	Some 550 similar machines from the company, based in Munich, Germany, are in use worldwide -- the largest number of them in the United States, according to Brainlab founder and chief executive officer Stefan Vilsmeier.
