9191	APW_ENG_20071009.0377.LDC2009T13	Coalition talks to form a new Belgian government made their first palpable progress in four months on Tuesday when Christian Democrats and Liberals agreed on a tougher asylum policy and limited economic migration.
9192	APW_ENG_20071009.0377.LDC2009T13	The agreement came 120 days after general elections and the continued stalemate between the Dutch-speaking and Francophone negotiators had raised fears that the bilingual country was about to break up.
9193	APW_ENG_20071009.0377.LDC2009T13	Despite the partial breakthrough, all the key issues on how to grant more autonomy to Dutch-speaking Flanders, Francophone Wallonia and bilingual Brussels while maintaining a sense of unity remained on the table.
