9695	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	LONDON 2007-12-14 15:05:28 UTC
9696	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	Following reports of depression and suicide in patients taking the anti-smoking drug Champix, the European Union's medicine authority has begun investigating its safety.
9697	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	On Friday, the European Medicines Agency asked Champix's maker, Pfizer Inc., to submit more information about the incidences of depression and suicide in patients taking the drug.
9698	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	"Based on a preliminary review of patient reports, our committee concluded this could signal a problem," said Monika Benstetter, a spokeswoman for the EU agency, which authorizes medicines for use in the 27-nation bloc.
9699	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	As part of its routine drug surveillance, the agency reviewed cases of Champix patients who had suicidal thoughts or attempted suicide from July, October and November.
9700	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	Champix was licensed for sale as a smoking cessation aid in the European Union last September.
9701	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	The drug works by binding to nicotine receptors in the brain, as well as by reducing the symptoms of withdrawal.
9702	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	Champix is available as tablets, and must be taken under medical supervision.
9703	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	At a meeting this month, the EU agency concluded that "there is a need to update the product information for Champix to warn doctors and patients that depression has been reported in patients who are trying to stop smoking using Champix."
9704	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	Pfizer said that it is working closely with the EU agency to review cases of depression and suicidal thoughts in patients taking Champix.
9705	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	"There is no scientific evidence establishing a causal relationship between Champix and these reported events," a company statement said.
9706	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	Experts acknowledged that establishing a causal relationship between taking Champix and depression or suicide would be difficult.
9707	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	American regulators have said that nicotine withdrawal could aggravate existing mental problems.
9708	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	But not all experts agreed.
9709	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	"Coming off smoking may make people depressed, but there's little evidence for the re-emergence of major psychiatric illness," said Dr. Peter Hajek, director of the Tobacco Dependence Research Unit at Queen Mary University Hospital in London.
9710	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	The EU agency's decision follows reports from the United States last month, where the drug is sold as Chantix, that at least one patient died while taking it.
9711	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	Family members of Dallas musician Carter Albrecht said the Pfizer drug may have caused the rage that ultimately led to his death.
9712	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	Albrecht was shot in the head in September by his girlfriend's neighbor as he tried to kick down the man's door.
9713	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	An autopsy report showed Albrecht's blood alcohol was three times the legal limit.
9714	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	The U.S. Food and Drug Administration said it asked Pfizer for information on additional cases that might be similar.
9715	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	In Europe, the EU agency has asked Pfizer to submit modified product information next week that warns doctors and patients about the potential for depression or suicide in patients taking Champix.
9716	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	The drug's current product information does not include any warnings about suicidal thoughts.
9717	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	Further action could be taken if warranted, Benstetter said.
9718	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	Hajek said that more information was needed before a real link between Champix and depression or suicide could be confirmed.
9719	APW_ENG_20071214.0802.LDC2009T13	"So far, these are just anecdotal reports," Hajek said.
