10168	APW_ENG_20080208.0306.LDC2009T13	Underlining the public gloom, after a brief holiday uptick, the mood of the country has returned to its level in November, with just 25 percent saying the country is headed in the right direction.
10169	APW_ENG_20080208.0306.LDC2009T13	President Harry Truman had the lowest rating ever in the Gallup Poll with 23 percent approval in 1952 during the Korean War
10170	APW_ENG_20080208.0306.LDC2009T13	President Richard Nixon reached 24 percent during the summer of 1974 before he resigned during the Watergate scandal.
