10352	APW_ENG_20080324.0919.LDC2009T13	CAIRO, Egypt 2008-03-24 18:23:26 UTC
10353	APW_ENG_20080324.0919.LDC2009T13	Al-Qaida No. 2 Ayman al-Zawahri called on Muslims to strike Jewish and American targets anywhere in the world in revenge for Israel's offensive in the Gaza Strip in an audiotape Monday, part of a new push by the terror network to use anger over the violence to rally support.
10354	APW_ENG_20080324.0919.LDC2009T13	The al-Zawahri tape came just days after two messages from Osama bin Laden, who called for a holy war to liberate the Palestinian territories and warned of a "severe" reaction against Europe over the recent publishing of cartoons seen as insulting Islam's Prophet Muhammad in Danish newspapers.
10355	APW_ENG_20080324.0919.LDC2009T13	The string of messages has raised fears al-Qaida could be planning new attacks against Israel or in the West -- or is seeking to inspire its sympathizers to carry out violence.
