10359	APW_ENG_20080324.0919.LDC2009T13	But al-Qaida is not known to have a direct presence in Israel or the Palestinian territories, though Israeli and Palestinian officials have at times warned it is seeking to.
10360	APW_ENG_20080324.0919.LDC2009T13	Al-Qaida sympathizers have often posted messages on Islamic militant Web forums asking why the terror network has not attacked Israel on its soil or gotten more involved on the Palestinian front.
10361	APW_ENG_20080324.0919.LDC2009T13	Bruce Hoffman, a counterterrorism expert, said that with al-Qaida in Iraq suffering setbacks, al-Qaida "has to look further afield and at least give an impression of an upward trajectory, that its operating across the Middle East."
10362	APW_ENG_20080324.0919.LDC2009T13	He pointed out that Al-Qaida's media arm, Al-Sahab, has dramatically stepped up its output of audio and video tapes, issuing an average of one every three days in 2007, more than double the 2006 rate.
10363	APW_ENG_20080324.0919.LDC2009T13	"There comes a time when you have to back up your words," said Hoffman, a professor at Washington's Georgetown University.
10364	APW_ENG_20080324.0919.LDC2009T13	"With the increased drumbeat of propoaganda ... it becomes an element of necessity, if you're talking so much you have to do something."
10365	APW_ENG_20080324.0919.LDC2009T13	"Perhaps they don't have the ability to attack the United States, so they may turn to the next best enemy, either Israel or Europe," he said.
10366	APW_ENG_20080324.0919.LDC2009T13	Al-Zawahri's call for attacks had a more immediate and urgent tone than past messages -- and he said attacks should not be limited to Israeli or Palestinian territory.
