10944	APW_ENG_20080502.1098.LDC2009T13	It goes 225 miles (362 kilometers) on one charge and can be fully recharged in 3.5 hours, which Tesla officials say should allow most people to drive it to work and back and recharge it at night like a cell phone.
10945	APW_ENG_20080502.1098.LDC2009T13	Driving from Los Angeles to San Francisco, however, would require stopping in, say, Fresno and plugging its adapter cord into a motel room wall socket.
