11156	APW_ENG_20080521.0453.LDC2009T13	Managers' assessment of their current economic situation also rose for the second time in four months.
11157	APW_ENG_20080521.0453.LDC2009T13	That subindex increased to 110.1 points from 108.4 points in April.
11158	APW_ENG_20080521.0453.LDC2009T13	"The renewed surprising upward movement in the Ifo business climate underscores that the German economy is currently better positioned than most of its European neighbors," said Alexander Koch, vice president and economist with UniCredit in Munich.
