11161	APW_ENG_20080521.0453.LDC2009T13	"Despite the current rise, the trend in the important expectations component points south and currently signals a softening in the growth dynamic to around potential by the second half of this year, with the outlook for expectations skewed to the downside in the months ahead."
11162	APW_ENG_20080521.0453.LDC2009T13	Ifo's report found that manufacturing companies were still planning moderate increases in employment, in part because "export opportunities continued to be appraised as good," the Munich-based agency said.
11163	APW_ENG_20080521.0453.LDC2009T13	Though it conceded that "firms are not quite as optimistic as in the previous month."
11164	APW_ENG_20080521.0453.LDC2009T13	Timo Klein, an analyst with Global Insight in Frankfurt, said the report's findings "were relatively uniform across sectors this time."
11165	APW_ENG_20080521.0453.LDC2009T13	"The wholesale and retail sectors both recovered after April's declines, driven by a more favorable assessment of their current situation but also by improved expectations," he said.
11166	APW_ENG_20080521.0453.LDC2009T13	"Retail expectations in particular remain clearly better than in late 2007, so that an improving trend for German consumer demand during the remainder of 2008 is becoming increasingly likely."
11167	APW_ENG_20080521.0453.LDC2009T13	The report was opposite of the latest survey of German investor confidence, which declined for a second straight month.
11168	APW_ENG_20080521.0453.LDC2009T13	On Tuesday, the ZEW institute's monthly index of investors' expectations for the German economy over the next six months dropped to minus 41.4 points in May from minus 40.7 points in April.
11169	APW_ENG_20080521.0453.LDC2009T13	The decline was worse than the minus 37 points analysts polled by Dow Jones Newswires had predicted.
