11270	APW_ENG_20080531.0724.LDC2009T13	In northern Belize, the National Emergency Management Organization expected about 4 inches (102 millimeters) of rain and warned of possible flooding around the Azul Hondo River.
11271	APW_ENG_20080531.0724.LDC2009T13	Rain and rough seas ruined vacations for tourists in Ambergis Caye.
11272	APW_ENG_20080531.0724.LDC2009T13	"I just came to lay in the sun and get a nice tan, but so far there hasn't been any sunshine," said Debbie Fountaineau, a police officer from Lake Charles, Louisiana, who arrived on the island Thursday.
11273	APW_ENG_20080531.0724.LDC2009T13	The storm was projected to weaken as it crosses the Yucatan before moving out into the Gulf of Mexico as a tropical depression early Sunday.
11274	APW_ENG_20080531.0724.LDC2009T13	There was chance it could strengthen back into a tropical storm before hitting Mexico again south of Veracruz on Wednesday, said Jamie Rhome, a meteorologist with the Hurricane Center.
11275	APW_ENG_20080531.0724.LDC2009T13	It was not expected to become a hurricane.
11276	APW_ENG_20080531.0724.LDC2009T13	At 2:00 p.m. EDT (1800 GMT) the storm's center was located about 50 miles (80 kilometers) northwest of Belize City.
11277	APW_ENG_20080531.0724.LDC2009T13	The storm was expected to stay well away from the U.S. Gulf Coast.
11278	APW_ENG_20080531.0724.LDC2009T13	"This is not a danger to the United States," said Rhome.
11279	APW_ENG_20080531.0724.LDC2009T13	---
11280	APW_ENG_20080531.0724.LDC2009T13	Associated Press writer Jorge Dominguez in Cancun, Mexico, contributed to this report.
