11378	APW_ENG_20080706.0397.LDC2009T13	That approach has earned criticism from U.S. officials, who say the deals will simply give time for militants to regroup and intensify attacks on foreign forces in neighboring Afghanistan.
11379	APW_ENG_20080706.0397.LDC2009T13	In late June, as militants in Pakistan's northwest increasingly began threatening the key city of Peshawar, the government launched a paramilitary operation in Khyber tribal region to flush out the extremists.
