12189	APW_ENG_20081001.0688.LDC2009T13	It's harder for European leaders to point the finger directly at the United States since many of their financiers participated in the recklessness.
12190	APW_ENG_20081001.0688.LDC2009T13	London was home to the division of failed insurer AIG that racked up huge losses on credit-default swaps, and many reputable European banks disregarded risk to load up on higher yielding subprime assets.
