12201	APW_ENG_20081001.0688.LDC2009T13	Countries with commodities-based economies are particularly vulnerable since more industrialized nations could reduce their demand for everything from soy to iron ore.
12202	APW_ENG_20081001.0688.LDC2009T13	"It doesn't seem fair to me that those of us who endured so much hunger in the 20th century, who began to improve in the 21st century, should have to suffer due to the international financial system," Silva said.
