12631	APW_ENG_20081118.0804.LDC2009T13	The exceptions were Nevada, California, Arizona and Virginia, where buyers have been able to snap up foreclosed homes at a bargain.
12632	APW_ENG_20081118.0804.LDC2009T13	"A very large proportion of distressed home sales are taking place at discounted prices compared to more normal conditions a year ago," Charles McMillan, the Realtors group's president, said in a statement.
12633	APW_ENG_20081118.0804.LDC2009T13	That's especially true in places like Sacramento and Riverside in California, where prices were down 37 percent and 39 percent, respectively, from last year.
12634	APW_ENG_20081118.0804.LDC2009T13	The two California cities had the largest annual price declines in the report.
12635	APW_ENG_20081118.0804.LDC2009T13	A nasty brew of strict lending standards, falling home values and a tough economy is filtering through the housing market.
12636	APW_ENG_20081118.0804.LDC2009T13	By the end of the year, foreclosure listing service RealtyTrac Inc. expects more than a million bank-owned properties to have piled up on the market, representing around a third of all properties for sale in the U.S.
12637	APW_ENG_20081118.0804.LDC2009T13	Meanwhile many economists believe the economy has fallen into a recession that could be the worst downturn in more than two decades.
12638	APW_ENG_20081118.0804.LDC2009T13	As layoffs accelerate, that's likely to put further downward pressure on housing prices.
12639	APW_ENG_20081118.0804.LDC2009T13	Freddie Mac said last week that rising unemployment rates, tightening credit and deteriorating economic conditions "contributed to a substantial increase in the number of delinquent loans," including loans made to borrowers with strong credit.
12640	APW_ENG_20081118.0804.LDC2009T13	Freddie Mac has 28,000 foreclosed properties on its books, while its sister company, Fannie Mae owns 67,500.
12641	APW_ENG_20081118.0804.LDC2009T13	On Tuesday, Rep. Barney Frank, chairman of the House Financial Services Committee, said "it is essential" to use some of the funds in the government's $700 billion financial rescue program to stem the tide of foreclosures.
