13753	LTW_ENG_20070415.0059.LDC2009T13	The agents submitted evidence this past winter to the Iraqi judiciary in a campaign to strip Sunni lawmaker Abdul Naser Janabi of his parliamentary immunity.
13754	LTW_ENG_20070415.0059.LDC2009T13	Janabi, a Sunni fundamentalist, is accused of being behind the killings of more than 150 Shiites in the triangle of death, a region just south of Baghdad, where Sunni extremists regularly target Shiites.
