15200	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	In previous years, the school's athletic trainer and Rotter's doctor would have monitored his symptoms -- if there were obvious signs, which is not always the case -- and made a determination about when he could return to action.
15201	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	Now Howard County schools can join other school districts that can make quantifiable decisions with the ImPACT (Immediate Post- Concussion Assessment and Cognitive Testing) program, a tool to help track recovery from concussions.
15202	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	The program, developed by Mark Lovell at the University of Pittsburgh Medical Center, is used by professional sports teams, colleges and hundreds of high schools in the United States.
15203	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	Howard began using it this school year, and it is free to students, with parental permission.
15204	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	Here's how it works: Before the season, an athlete takes the computerized ImPACT test, which, in part, measures his memory and reaction time after being shown a series of words, designs, patterns and symbols.
15205	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	It takes about 25 minutes.
15206	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	There is no particular score for which to strive
15207	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	each athlete's results provide a baseline of information.
15208	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	"It definitely tests you," Rotter said.
15209	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	If the athlete experiences a head injury, he retakes the test to see how his results compare with his baseline reading.
15210	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	Is there a lapse in memory?
15211	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	Reaction time?
15212	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	Some other decline in performance?
15213	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	If his retest results fall markedly short of his baseline numbers, he probably will be deemed not ready to play.
15214	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	The athlete will continue to sit out until his ImPACT scores are close to his pre-concussion results.
15215	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	The ImPACT test findings remove some of the guesswork about whether an athlete is fit to resume play, and the graphic representation of results makes it easy to explain to athletes and their parents why the athlete might or might not be fully recovered from a head injury.
15216	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	"There's a real gap in the knowledge of this injury," said Gerry Gioia, director of neuropsychology and director of the Safe Concussion Outcome, Recovery and Education (SCORE) Program at Children's National Medical Center in Washington.
15217	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	"What happens is families and kids are getting lots of different messages about whether they can go back to play or not, and many times it's not based on any objective or systematic data."
15218	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	To learn more about the ImPACT program, and to take the test ourselves, we caught up with Rotter, 16, and Hammond athletic trainer Tim Happel on Friday when Rotter was retaking the test for the second time since sustaining a concussion late last month.
15219	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	Rotter first got concussed in first grade in a bike accident.
15220	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	He lost his short-term memory for a few days.
15221	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	A person who sustains a concussion can be more vulnerable to concussion than those who have not sustained such an injury.
15222	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	"Oh, another butterfly gave you a concussion?"
15223	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	a buddy said to Rotter recently, jokingly suggesting that the middle linebacker- offensive lineman and lacrosse defender, known for his physical playing style, is soft.
15224	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	When Rotter, who is enrolled in honors courses, is concussed, he suffers from headaches and a lack of concentration.
15225	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	"It feels like you have a haze over you, a fog, kind of," he said, adding that his grade-point average dipped from about a 3.57 to a 2.71 in the fall when he had trouble focusing after his football concussion.
15226	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	"He's in all really, really intense classes, so concussions have much more effect there than on the field," said his mother, Julie.
15227	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	Rotter could tell when he took the first retest April 2 that he was not particularly sharp.
15228	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	He noticed further improvement Friday afternoon, taking it for a second time since his lacrosse concussion.
15229	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	But before clearing him to play, Happel wanted to consult with Gioia, who helped develop the concussion treatment program for Howard schools.
15230	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	(Gioia's children play sports at Mount Hebron High in Ellicott City, Md.)
15231	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	"It seemed like I could remember the shapes a lot easier," Rotter said after his second retest.
15232	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	"I was a lot faster, it felt like.
15233	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	It was a pretty obvious difference."
15234	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	Mike Williams, coordinator of athletics for Howard schools, said that the county's dozen high schools have tested an average of about 200 athletes each.
15235	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	With the program becoming more established, he expects that number to grow to 400 or more next school year.
15236	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	"They used to say after two days you could return" from a concussion, Williams said.
15237	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	"Then it went to a week.
15238	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	Now research shows that with high school students, their brains are still developing, and a sustained concussion in a high school student can impact their learning and development for a lifetime.
15239	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	When we saw that, that's what really sold us.
15240	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	It's not a perfect science, but it's the best thing out there."
15241	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	The cost of the program is $9,000 for the software, about $750 for each of Howard's 12 high schools.
15242	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	But for school systems without certified athletic trainers, administering and interpreting the tests could be a problem.
15243	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	Howard has a trainer.
15244	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	For athletes itching to get back on the field, the ImPACT test can be friend or foe: friend if it raises no red flags, which might result in getting back sooner, or foe if the athlete feels fine -- or is downplaying symptoms, which is common -- but falls short of baseline benchmarks when retaking the test.
15245	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	Oh, and don't try to lowball your initial ImPACT test.
15246	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	Not only could it be hazardous to your health, it could be embarrassing.
15247	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	Gioia said the test has indicators that expose sandbaggers.
15248	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	"I feel like (the ImPACT test) is holding me back a little bit," Rotter said, "but I'm also glad it exists.
15249	LTW_ENG_20080424.0004.LDC2009T13	Because if it didn't exist, I'd be back on the field and getting another concussion and be in a worse state."
