15964	NYT_ENG_20070126.0179.LDC2009T13	Kosovo, the size of Connecticut, has roughly 2 million people, 90 percent of whom are ethnic Albanian Muslims, a legacy of Ottoman rule.
15965	NYT_ENG_20070126.0179.LDC2009T13	But it is also the land of Serbia's medieval kings and the site of many of the Serbs' most important churches.
15966	NYT_ENG_20070126.0179.LDC2009T13	It was an autonomous region within the Yugoslav federation until 1989, when Slobodan Milosevic asserted Belgrade's authority over the territory.
