16862	NYT_ENG_20070411.0190.LDC2009T13	Sometimes they get very emotional in the way that they characterize people's motives and actions."
16863	NYT_ENG_20070411.0190.LDC2009T13	"I wasn't there," Perdue told reporters, "but I've made motions before that didn't get a second.
16864	NYT_ENG_20070411.0190.LDC2009T13	It's not always fun, but that's the way our government works."
16865	NYT_ENG_20070411.0190.LDC2009T13	Rep. Al Williams (D-Midway), the head of Georgia's Legislative Black Caucus, said he supports hanging Coretta Scott King's portrait in the Capitol but he disagreed with Abdul-Salaam's comparison with the Imus controversy.
