17143	NYT_ENG_20070515.0215.LDC2009T13	The latest twist in the Jamaican police investigation into the death of Bob Woolmer, the Pakistani cricket coach found unconscious in his hotel room in March during the Cricket World Cup, may be that he was not murdered at all.
17144	NYT_ENG_20070515.0215.LDC2009T13	Quoting people close to Dr. Nat Carey, a top British pathologist called in to review the postmortem on Woolmer, newspapers in Britain, where Woolmer was from, and Jamaica, where he died, are raising questions about the Jamaican authorities' claim that Woolmer was strangled.
