17583	NYT_ENG_20070703.0261.LDC2009T13	We know that," Crist said at his news conference.
17584	NYT_ENG_20070703.0261.LDC2009T13	"But to continue to rely on foreign oil and coal, I don't think is in the best interests of our state."
17585	NYT_ENG_20070703.0261.LDC2009T13	Crist's anti-coal crusade isn't over.
17586	NYT_ENG_20070703.0261.LDC2009T13	Last month his Department of Environmental Protection withdrew support for a permit for the Seminole Electric Co. to add onto a coal-burning plant in Putnam County.
17587	NYT_ENG_20070703.0261.LDC2009T13	Because the Putnam plant is an addition to an existing plant, environmental groups had not lined up against it as they did the Everglades and Taylor County plants.
17588	NYT_ENG_20070703.0261.LDC2009T13	It seemed to face smooth sailing.
17589	NYT_ENG_20070703.0261.LDC2009T13	But now the DEP has raised a major hurdle, filing a legal motion that says the state needs to consider limiting the plant's greenhouse gases.
17590	NYT_ENG_20070703.0261.LDC2009T13	Meanwhile the agenda for next week's climate summit calls for discussions of clean energy sources .
