17618	NYT_ENG_20070709.0030.LDC2009T13	In that, we have abided by the steady and universal counsel of western political and spiritual leadership.
17619	NYT_ENG_20070709.0030.LDC2009T13	After all, Islamist terrorists have been mostly young, variously disaffected, indifferently educated, to whom the innate discipline of reason is not second nature, or even third.
17620	NYT_ENG_20070709.0030.LDC2009T13	Muslim, yes, usually Middle Eastern, yet a breed apart.
