17643	NYT_ENG_20070711.0048.LDC2009T13	Thanks to the gift from Jon and Johnette Jarvis, who own and operate farming and ranching interests in the Texas Panhandle, the university has established an endowment to provide some needy students with rings each year.
17644	NYT_ENG_20070711.0048.LDC2009T13	The gift comes as donors throughout the country are pouring billions into their alma maters to build fancy laboratories and entice top-notch professors and ultra-bright students.
