18616	NYT_ENG_20071124.0092.LDC2009T13	He sponsored the
18617	NYT_ENG_20071124.0092.LDC2009T13	legislation that created Workforce Florida.
18618	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	LESSONS FROM ROSIE, REVISITED
18619	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	Say what you will about Judith Regan -- most people have -- she knows her way around a rip-roaring read.
18620	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	The complaint in her $100 million civil suit against the News Corp., with its riveting passages about corporate connivance, public malfeasance and ill- fated romance, is as much a page-turner as any of the dozens of salacious best sellers she produced at ReganBooks, her imprint at HarperCollins before she was fired at the end of last year.
18621	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	But the deeper I went in the complaint, the more I felt I had read this book before.
18622	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	The narrative -- about a talented but unpredictable impresario who joined forces with a media company with a great deal of fanfare before a huge, ugly divorce -- mirrored the confrontation between Rosie O'Donnell and Gruner &amp
18623	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	amp
18624	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	Jahr USA in 2002.
18625	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	The parallels are not exact -- it was Gruner &amp
18626	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	amp
18627	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	Jahr that sued O'Donnell on the grounds of breach of contract, while Regan is the one doing the suing, claiming that she had been defamed by News Corp. officials -- but they are instructive, especially for the News Corp.
18628	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	In the case of O'Donnell, it was her insistence on making sure that the old McCall's magazine, renamed Rosie, reflected her take on the world, including putting herself on the cover with an upraised and bandaged middle finger to depict her fight against a staph infection.
18629	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	Regan, who asserted in her suit that she had sold more than $1 billion worth of books, was fired after her plans to publish a hypothetical confession from O.J. Simpson caused an uproar, and HarperCollins then said she had made anti-Semitic remarks during the ensuing dust-up.
18630	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	Both O'Donnell and Regan entertained settlement discussions before deciding to press on, in part because they could not abide by nondisclosure agreements.
18631	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	These are not people who go away quietly.
18632	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	In O'Donnell's case, the trial played a role in the eventual shut down of Gruner &amp
18633	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	amp
18634	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	Jahr's American division.
18635	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	No one, including me, is suggesting that Regan will take down a company with a market capitalization of $66 billion.
18636	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	Still, what seems like a nuisance can become a significant problem in court.
18637	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	The News Corp., a tough outfit that does not embarrass or scare easily, would still seem to have a lot more to lose than Regan.
18638	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	Much continues to be made of the fact that Regan is sitting on explosive allegations about Rudolph W. Giuliani, former mayor of New York and a presidential candidate.
18639	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	In her lawsuit, she claims that she was encouraged to lie by a News Corp. official about the activities of Bernard B. Kerik, a former romantic interest who was also the former New York police commissioner, a candidate for Homeland Security secretary and a Giuliani business partner.
18640	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	She further said the company had delivered on a promise to systematically smear her reputation if she did not go along.
18641	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	News Corp. officials point out that Rupert Murdoch has never been a supporter of Giuliani and describe the accusation as silly, but Regan steadfastly maintains that she has the goods to support her allegations.
18642	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	"Judith Regan would not have brought this lawsuit unless she had explicit, unambiguous evidence to back it up," said a spokesman on her behalf.
18643	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	Of course, you can say anything in a lawsuit, and Regan remains coy about the exact nature of the accusations.
18644	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	A spokesman for the News Corp. pointed out that the case was a long way from a trial and added that the company was "highly dismissive of her complaint and the company will vigorously defend itself in this action."
18645	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	Before the trial involving O'Donnell and her former partners -- the damages sought were also $100 million -- I can remember how executives of Gruner &amp
18646	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	amp
18647	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	Jahr expressed the same kind of confidence.
18648	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	Then O'Donnell went to work on the witness stand, saying precisely what was on her mind.
18649	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	It was a field day for working reporters (I was one of them), with mud and tears flying in all directions before the presiding judge decided to put a pox on both their houses and gave each side nothing.
18650	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	But Gruner &amp
18651	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	amp
18652	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	Jahr USA never recovered from the trial, which included the revelation that it had manipulated financial and circulation figures.
18653	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	If Regan and the News Corp. don't settle, the discovery and trial could be embarrassing for reasons that have nothing to do with Giuliani.
18654	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	Regan has turned down a settlement of more than $6 million, according to news articles.
18655	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	It's not that her particular claims about the News Corp. have to stick.
18656	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	Pull back the blankets on any enterprise -- the book business, the movie business, what the heck, the news business -- and some common industry practices are not going to look so good in the cold light of the courtroom.
18657	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	She was in a position to know a lot, and she may be in the mood to tell all of it.
18658	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	"We don't know the truth of the various allegations, but other things may come out that are not directly related to what she is suing for," said Mark C. Zauderer, a Manhattan trial lawyer.
18659	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	"You have to consider the financial exposure versus the reputational exposure of not settling."
18660	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	Regan, perhaps more so than O'Donnell, has a penchant for aggression matched only by a knack for surprises.
18661	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	After it became apparent that the public found the idea of the Simpson book and an accompanying interview abhorrent, she suggested that as a victim of abuse, she had decided to "sit face to face with the killer, because I wanted him, and the other men who broke my heart and your hearts, to tell the truth, to confess their sins, to do penance."
18662	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	Those religious motifs were on display more recently in a short as-told-to article in Harper's Bazaar in which she posed as St. Sebastian, replete with bloody arrows accessorizing a fetching white gown.
18663	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	"People were afraid to come to my defense, and they betrayed me right and left," she said in the article.
18664	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	"They wanted to save their own hides.
18665	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	Or they were promised something better.
18666	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	I don't know, whatever the reason, it disappointed me to the bone and broke my heart."
18667	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	Regan's profound public woundedness has her healing on a number of fronts, including calling on her former training in the Vassar Madrigals to record a version of "My Way."
18668	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	She is said to be contemplating recording an album of standards ("Call Me Irresponsible" might make a good B-side to "My Way.")
18669	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	She also started filming a documentary in China, and she must be checking the Amazon best-seller list with satisfaction.
18670	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	The Simpson book, "If I Did It," continues to sell, albeit for another company and with the profits accruing to the Goldman family.
18671	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	In a sense, Regan was dispossessed for doing precisely what she was good at, which is to pick books that stir controversy and sales.
18672	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	Gruner &amp
18673	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	amp
18674	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	Jahr grabbed onto O'Donnell to help revive McCall's, a dying women's magazine, because just about everything she does kicks up public interest.
18675	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	But both women's abilities to rivet public attention with their brand of psychodrama is a weapon that will point in all directions.
18676	NYT_ENG_20071202.0121.LDC2009T13	So before News Corp. executives decide to tangle with Regan in court, perhaps they should remember why they hired her in the first place.
18677	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	LA-TROXLER-COLUMN-STP
18678	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	Hey, do you mind if we take a whack at this business about "intelligent design" vs. "evolution"?
18679	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	The debate flared up again in Florida last week.
18680	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	Here's my fix.
18681	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	They're not opposite things.
18682	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	They are entirely separate matters.
18683	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	Let's deal with them separately.
18684	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	So if you say you want to "teach intelligent design" in the public schools, hey, that's fine by me, up to a point.
18685	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	I would address it in a few paragraphs early on about the kinds of things that people believe.
18686	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	I would say that lots of people believe that our universe has a creator, and a purpose.
18687	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	For further info, I would say, check out the religion of your choice, if you choose one.
18688	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	And if you don't, and don't believe that, that's fine too this is a public school, and we are not taking sides here.
18689	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	You want more than that?
18690	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	Okeydoke.
18691	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	We could also throw in the part about how some people believe the universe is too complicated to have occurred by accident.
18692	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	Eyeballs, brains, cell nuclei, all of that kind of stuff.
18693	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	That's perfectly true, too.
18694	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	I mean, it's true that lots of people make that argument.
18695	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	As to whether we can ever settle the argument, beats me.
18696	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	Now we come to the unrelated "evolution" part of the science curriculum, and here is what I would teach:
18697	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	No matter how the world came into being, as best we can tell, life here on Earth has changed over long periods of time.
18698	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	It's a fact.
18699	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	We know it.
18700	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	We have dug it up.
18701	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	We have taken a good gander at it.
18702	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	Lots of guys who looked kind of like us, but who weren't us, used to walk around.
18703	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	Lots of old stuff is gone.
18704	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	Lots of new stuff is here.
18705	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	Saying this is not an attack on religion.
18706	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	It has nothing to say about whether God created the universe.
18707	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	Nothing.
18708	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	Zippo.
18709	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	It's just as silly to use science to deny God as it is to use faith to deny science.
18710	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	And yet, if you are still determined to have a fight, you could say:
18711	NYT_ENG_20071209.0046.LDC2009T13	"The book of Genesis tells me that God fashioned man out of clay and made the world in six days.
