18766	NYT_ENG_20071215.0082.LDC2009T13	Frustration at the U.N. peacekeeping force and the dozens of aid organizations working in North Kivu province, in eastern Congo, is rising as violence increases, the number of displaced people here creeps toward 1 million, and the pace of assistance, especially to those fleeing the fighting in the past few weeks, lags.
18767	NYT_ENG_20071215.0082.LDC2009T13	Many Congolese want the U.N. peacekeepers to intervene more forcefully and fight beside the Congolese army against the rebel forces of Laurent Nkunda, a renegade general who refuses to merge his troops into the national armed forces.
