18769	NYT_ENG_20071215.0082.LDC2009T13	Congo's army has proved unable to beat back the rebels, and the fighting in the past year has displaced 425,000 people.
18770	NYT_ENG_20071215.0082.LDC2009T13	The U.N. force has a strong mandate in Congo to use force to protect civilians, and it has pledged to defend Goma and the camps around it from being overrun by rebels.
18771	NYT_ENG_20071215.0082.LDC2009T13	It is also required to work with the Congolese army to establish security, which has led to the expectation in a population weary from more than a decade of conflict that the U.N. force here, known by its acronym, MONUC, would help defeat the rebels.
