18887	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	The minimal evidence found at the scene included a shoe and blood in the 25-foot-wide moat that surrounds the tigers' grotto, raising questions about what role, if any, the victims might have had in accidentally helping the animal escape.
18888	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	The three victims, all young men from San Jose, were visiting the zoo together.
18889	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	They were each present when the tiger escaped, killed 17-year-old Carlos Sousa Jr. with a savage slash to the throat, and injured the other two.
18890	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	The names of the survivors, who are brothers ages 19 and 23, have not been released by authorities.
18891	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	The injured victims fled, and the tiger apparently followed them under rapidly darkening skies for 300 yards down a zoo pathway.
18892	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	As the tiger cornered and attacked one of the brothers, four police officers arrived, distracted the animal and shot it dead.
18893	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	Zoo officials said they are trying to figure out how the 4-year- old Siberian tiger named Tatiana escaped from her enclosure shortly after the zoo's 5 p.m. closing time.
18894	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	No doors to the grotto had been left ajar, they said.
18895	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	The animal is the same one who attacked a zookeeper almost exactly a year ago.
18896	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	Officials speculated that one of the victims may have been dangling a leg or other body part over the 14-foot grotto wall and that Tatiana latched onto the limb and climbed out.
18897	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	Police sources said a footprint had been found on a metal fence, suggesting that someone had climbed it to get closer to the big cats.
18898	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	Zoo Director Manuel Mollinedo said it was also likely that the animal was provoked.
18899	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	"Somebody created a situation that really agitated her and gave her some sort of a method to break out," Mollinedo said.
18900	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	"There is no possible way the cat could have made it out of there in a single leap.
18901	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	I would surmise that there was help.
18902	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	"A couple of feet dangling over the edge could possibly have done it," he added.
18903	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	Sources said pinecones and sticks that were found in the moat might have been thrown at the animal.
18904	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	Those items could not have landed in the grotto naturally, they said.
18905	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	However, police Sgt. Neville Gittens maintained that there was no reason to think that the victims were taunting the tiger.
18906	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	The two survivors were in serious but stable condition Wednesday following surgery at San Francisco General Hospital, doctors said.
18907	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	The zoo, which closed Wednesday, will remain shut today so that police continue their investigation.
18908	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	Mollinedo said he hopes the zoo will reopen Friday, but the tigers and lions will not be on display for at least a week.
18909	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	The hunt for the escaped tiger Tuesday was confused and chaotic, with police and paramedics frantically scrambling through the 1,000-acre zoo grounds to locate victims after discovering Sousa's body.
18910	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	There are no surveillance cameras pointed at the big cats' grottos, so officers could not find out from zoo security guards what animal or animals had escaped.
18911	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	Initial calls for help didn't say what sort of animal had escaped, sources said.
18912	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	The lack of cameras also has made it difficult to ascertain how the attacks occurred.
18913	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	Police said the investigation will focus on physical evidence collected at the zoo, witness statements, an autopsy of the victim and the necropsy of the tiger.
18914	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	New cameras and a metal barrier will be installed to protect the public from the tigers and lions, Mollinedo said.
18915	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	As darkness deepened Tuesday, officers found that the modest level of zoo lighting was insufficient to illuminate the trees, foliage and public areas where they initially feared that more animals might be lurking or more victims might be found.
18916	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	Firefighters standing on tall ladders outside the zoo illuminated the grounds with portable lights to help the search.
18917	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	"We didn't know how many tigers were out," Mollinedo said.
18918	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	"I (was) under the impression we had two or three cats escaping.
18919	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	There was a sense of paranoia around here."
18920	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	Investigators canvassed the zoo for hours Wednesday morning before finally determining that nobody else had been hurt.
18921	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	A Fire Department source said three paramedics found Sousa's body, with a wide gash across the neck, lying near the grotto.
18922	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	The enclosure is surrounded by a 25- to 30-foot-wide moat and a 14-foot-high wall.
18923	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	The paramedics and an ambulance driver were told of additional victims outside the Terrace Cafe restaurant, about 300 yards east.
18924	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	When they arrived, they found the tiger standing over one of the brothers.
18925	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	The paramedics and driver were soon joined by the four police officers, who distracted the tiger with the red lights of their two patrol cars before shooting her to death with their .40-caliber handguns.
18926	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	Gittens said the officers did not want to shoot the animal while she was sitting next to the victim.
18927	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	"I can only imagine the patrons walking around, and suddenly seeing this tiger," he said.
