18931	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	It's not known why the tiger singled out the three visitors or why she tracked down the two wounded victims, apparently ignoring other zoo patrons.
18932	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	Rochelle Dicker, an emergency room surgeon at San Francisco General Hospital who operated on the victims, said Wednesday that the two survivors were recovering remarkably well.
18933	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	They were awake and stable, Dicker said.
