18943	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	Mollinedo said the zoo has a response team armed with tranquilizers and firearms, but that the scene unfolded "so quickly that the officers found (Tatiana) first."
18944	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	This is the second time in just over a year that this same tiger attacked a human.
18945	NYT_ENG_20071226.0223.LDC2009T13	On Dec. 22, 2006, Tatiana chewed the flesh off zookeeper Lori Komejan's arm in front of about 50 visitors lingering in the Lion House after the cats were fed.
