19590	NYT_ENG_20080425.0070.LDC2009T13	More like one endlessly patient young woman who answers the phone and greets strangers walking through the door with cheery aplomb.
19591	NYT_ENG_20080425.0070.LDC2009T13	At first glance, this conservatively appointed office suite - muted carpeting, framed Ronald Reagan photo on the wall - in a highrise office building could be home to any of the countless well-connected doctors, lawyers or investment professionals who discretely keep Atlanta ticking.
19592	NYT_ENG_20080425.0070.LDC2009T13	Instead, it's the epicenter of a political earthquake.
19593	NYT_ENG_20080425.0070.LDC2009T13	Maybe.
19594	NYT_ENG_20080425.0070.LDC2009T13	"There are several things we want to get in place before we would make an announcement," Bob Barr says during a recent interview at his consulting firm, Liberty Strategies LLC in Atlanta.
