19604	NYT_ENG_20080425.0070.LDC2009T13	"I'm fed up with the two-party system."
19605	NYT_ENG_20080425.0070.LDC2009T13	'Bless their hearts'
19606	NYT_ENG_20080425.0070.LDC2009T13	He's apparently not alone.
19607	NYT_ENG_20080425.0070.LDC2009T13	The exploratory committee polled likely voters and found that 7 percent said they would vote for unannounced candidate Barr.
19608	NYT_ENG_20080425.0070.LDC2009T13	Next up was a George Will column about Barr's potentially "ruinous" impact on presumed Republican nominee John McCain's chances.
19609	NYT_ENG_20080425.0070.LDC2009T13	So, has Barr heard anything - veiled threats, promises of plum ambassadorships - from the McCain forces lately?
19610	NYT_ENG_20080425.0070.LDC2009T13	"No, not directly," replies Barr, who had to give up his weekly op-ed column in The Atlanta Journal-Constitution when he launched the exploratory committee.
19611	NYT_ENG_20080425.0070.LDC2009T13	Of the few "more traditional" Republicans he has heard discouraging words from: "They have this sort of idea in their minds, bless their hearts, that nobody should do anything to upset the Republican nominee.
19612	NYT_ENG_20080425.0070.LDC2009T13	This notion that the political world swirls around two galaxies only, Republican and Democrat only, and anybody else who enters that fray is going to affect the other two and that's bad - that's a very myopic notion."
19613	NYT_ENG_20080425.0070.LDC2009T13	That's classic Barr, from the slightly withering "bless their hearts" to the almost reflexively Republican use of "Democrat" as an adjective.
19614	NYT_ENG_20080425.0070.LDC2009T13	(Also on the wall of the onetime House Manager: A framed display - including photos and gallery tickets - commemorating President Bill Clinton's impeachment trial.)
19615	NYT_ENG_20080425.0070.LDC2009T13	But he also sounds - and behaves - like a man with more than just a notion about running for president.
19616	NYT_ENG_20080425.0070.LDC2009T13	There's the impressive Web site that went live seemingly while Barr was still having a parking stub validated.
