19800	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	MOVING UGGLA FROM NO. 2 IN LINEUP PAYING POWERFUL DIVIDENDS
19801	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	Cox News Service
19802	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	MIAMI GARDENS, Fla. - Smartest lineup move the Marlins made this year?
19803	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	Switching second baseman Dan Uggla from second in the batting order to a place where he can worry less about getting on base and swing away.
19804	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	After he moved out of the second spot May 2 - he currently is batting fifth - Uggla hit .439 with eight home runs and 17 RBI in his next 12 games.
19805	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	Uggla led the first-place Marlins in batting average (.316), home runs (13) and RBI (31) as they began a three-game series with his former club, the Arizona Diamondbacks, Tuesday at Dolphin Stadium.
19806	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	He also leads in strikeouts (44), less than ideal for the No. 2 spot, with its greater emphasis on setting the table rather than clearing it.
19807	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	"Up until this year, I wouldn't have believed it made any difference," Uggla's father, John, said from home in Columbia, Tenn. "He's always hit second.
19808	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	He gets more at-bats that way.
19809	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	Last year they dropped him down for a few games and he didn't do that well.
19810	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	But now, wow.
19811	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	The whole thing is kind of amazing to me his power numbers are so good."
19812	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	Dan Uggla himself isn't sold on the idea that batting order matters that much - he points out he still hit 31 homers last year.
19813	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	"It hasn't changed my approach at all," Uggla said.
19814	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	"The only thing it has done for me is it's given me more RBI opportunities, hitting behind (Jeremy) Hermida, Hanley (Ramirez) and those guys.
19815	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	There's a good chance those guys are going to be on base by the time I get up there."
19816	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	But the statistics suggest moving him down was the right thing.
19817	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	His batting average has climbed from a lackluster .245 last season.
19818	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	He is waiting for pitches he can punish and the team is benefiting more when he does connect.
19819	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	"I don't know if it's the lineup change, but he's been swinging it pretty good," manager Fredi Gonzales said.
19820	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	It's a wiser handling of a rarity at his position, a power guy at second base.
19821	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	Uggla is on pace to become the first second baseman to pound 80 or more extra-base hits in consecutive seasons since Hall of Famer Rogers Hornsby in the 1920s.
19822	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	Uggla, 28, has a higher slugging and on-base percentage than Jeff Kent did at the same age, and Kent has been one of the archetypal big-stick second baseman.
19823	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	This year, Uggla ranks in the top two with Chase Utley in a slew of offensive power categories among all second basemen.
19824	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	The Diamondbacks didn't see that coming when they failed to protect him on their roster in 2005.
19825	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	Facing his former team is just a chance to see old friends, Uggla insists, downplaying the idea he has any extra incentive to play well.
19826	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	At the same time, there's an occasional hint he has not entirely forgotten the history when the topic turns to his fielding.
19827	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	"Shoot, I only made 11 errors last year," Uggla said.
19828	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	"I don't think that's really considered a liability.
19829	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	That was supposed to be my downfall, why the D'backs never really gave me a chance because I couldn't play defense."
19830	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	Actually, Uggla is right that he doesn't have much left to prove to the Diamondbacks.
19831	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	The team that matters now is the Marlins.
19832	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	The Marlins, who announced a long-term, $70 million deal with shortstop Hanley Ramirez during the weekend, have signaled no immediate plans to lock up other players.
19833	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	President of Baseball Operations Larry Beinfest made no other recommendations for multiyear deals, team owner Jeffrey Loria said.
19834	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	Uggla is eligible for arbitration next year.
19835	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	His fielding (five errors this season, tied for fifth-most at his position), his age (four years older than Ramirez) and other factors all play into the calculations.
19836	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	The team will eventually have to decide whether to offer him a multiyear deal or just go year to year until he's eligible for free agency in a little more than three years.
19837	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	Certainly he's a bargain now at $417,000.
19838	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	The Marlins briefly considered moving Uggla to third base when they traded Miguel Cabrera.
19839	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	The franchise has infield prospect Chris Coghlan waiting in the wings.
19840	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	The long-term outlook depends in part on the chemistry up the middle with Ramirez.
19841	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	That chemistry can't always be measured in the score book.
19842	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	Uggla admitted a "bonehead play" in the opener of the team's most recent series, failing to cover second on what should have been a double play.
19843	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	Instead, it led to two unearned runs by Kansas City after a double-clutching Ramirez botched a throw to first.
19844	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	At other moments, the double-play tandem has worked more smoothly.
19845	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	"As far as them offering any kind of long-term deal, that's totally their call," Uggla said.
19846	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	"If they want to do it, great.
19847	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	Obviously I love it down here.
19848	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	I love the guys.
19849	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	We'll just have to wait to see what happens.
19850	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	It's too early to tell right now."
19851	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	It is not too early to see one thing - moving Uggla down in the batting order has helped the Marlins move up.
19852	NYT_ENG_20080520.0062.LDC2009T13	And if he can keep it up, he will make a powerful case that the Marlins should not let him move on.
