20631	NYT_ENG_20081224.0045.LDC2009T13	RECIPE-CRABS-HNS
20632	NYT_ENG_20081224.0045.LDC2009T13	STUFFED CRABS -- 1 dozen boiled crabs 4 tablespoons butter, divided use 1/2 cup minced onion 1/4 cup minced celery 1/4 cup minced bell pepper 2 cloves garlic, minced 2 tablespoons finely chopped parsley 1 egg, beaten 1/2 teaspoon salt 1/2 teaspoon pepper 1/2 teaspoon Creole seasoning 1 tablespoon lemon juice 1 1/4 cups seasoned bread crumbs, divided use
20633	NYT_ENG_20081224.0045.LDC2009T13	Pick crabs, saving meat and fat.
20634	NYT_ENG_20081224.0045.LDC2009T13	Clean the back shells of 6 to 8 crabs, depending on size, discarding all else.
20635	NYT_ENG_20081224.0045.LDC2009T13	Set aside.
20636	NYT_ENG_20081224.0045.LDC2009T13	Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
20637	NYT_ENG_20081224.0045.LDC2009T13	Melt 2 tablespoons butter in large, heavy skillet and saute onion, celery and bell pepper until soft.
20638	NYT_ENG_20081224.0045.LDC2009T13	Add garlic and saute briefly.
20639	NYT_ENG_20081224.0045.LDC2009T13	In medium bowl, mix crabmeat and fat, parsley, egg, onion mixture, salt, pepper, Creole seasoning, lemon juice and 1 cup bread crumbs.
20640	NYT_ENG_20081224.0045.LDC2009T13	Divide into 6 to 8 portions.
20641	NYT_ENG_20081224.0045.LDC2009T13	Stuff mixture into shells and top with remaining bread crumbs.
20642	NYT_ENG_20081224.0045.LDC2009T13	Dot with remaining 2 tablespoons of butter, cut into bits.
20643	NYT_ENG_20081224.0045.LDC2009T13	Bake until stuffed crabs are nicely browned, about 20 to 30 minutes.
20644	NYT_ENG_20081224.0045.LDC2009T13	Makes 6 to 8 servings.
20645	NYT_ENG_20081224.0045.LDC2009T13	Approximate nutritional values per serving: 160 calories (43.3 percent calories from fat), 9 g protein, 13 g carbohydrate, 1 g sugar, 1 g dietary fiber, 8 g fat, 65 mg cholesterol, 640 mg sodium.
