20921	XIN_ENG_20070619.0425.LDC2009T13	The firm's 2007 North America Airline Satisfaction Study measured the overall customer satisfaction based on performance in seven measures, including cost and fees, flight crew, in-flight services, aircraft, boarding/deplaning/baggage, check-in and reservation.
20922	XIN_ENG_20070619.0425.LDC2009T13	JetBlue Airways ranked highest overall for the third consecutive year, earning the highest ranking for low-cost carriers -- defined as airlines that operate single-cabin aircraft with typically low fares -- in 2006 and 2007.
