21007	XIN_ENG_20070808.0243.LDC2009T13	According to statistics of China's Ministry of Commerce, it reached to 160.8 billion U.S. dollars in 2006, and the figure is expected to surpass 180 billion U.S. dollars this year.
21008	XIN_ENG_20070808.0243.LDC2009T13	Now China is the fourth biggest trade partner of ASEAN, and ASEAN the fifth of China.
21009	XIN_ENG_20070808.0243.LDC2009T13	In 2002, China became the first country to sign agreement with ASEAN on building Free Trade Area (FTA), which will be completed by 2010.
21010	XIN_ENG_20070808.0243.LDC2009T13	In the past five years, taxes of about 7,000 kinds of goods has lowered down, scale of mutually direct investment went on bulge, China-ASEAN Expo which held in China's Nanning every year since 2004 has become an important stage for bilateral trade and communications.
21011	XIN_ENG_20070808.0243.LDC2009T13	People of both sides have benefited a lot in the FTA.
21012	XIN_ENG_20070808.0243.LDC2009T13	South Korea and Japan also do not want to lag behind in term of 10+3 cooperation.
21013	XIN_ENG_20070808.0243.LDC2009T13	A free-trade deal covering merchandise between South Korea and ASEAN, excluding Thailand, came into force on June 1.
21014	XIN_ENG_20070808.0243.LDC2009T13	Negotiations covering services and investment will end by the end of this year.
21015	XIN_ENG_20070808.0243.LDC2009T13	The trade volume of South Korea and ASEAN reached 53.5 billion U.S. dollars, account for one tenth of South Korea's total trade, in the year 2005.
21016	XIN_ENG_20070808.0243.LDC2009T13	Investment of 12.5 billion U.S. dollars from South Korea flew to ASEAN in 2006.
21017	XIN_ENG_20070808.0243.LDC2009T13	Although Japan has not signed free trade deal with ASEAN, it has been one of the countries that invest most in ASEAN members in the past 30 years.
21018	XIN_ENG_20070808.0243.LDC2009T13	In a healthy competition of the three countries so far to boost trade and investment in ASEAN, economic integration in East Asia becomes foreseeable.
21019	XIN_ENG_20070808.0243.LDC2009T13	As the cooperation is deepening and broadening, the concerned topics of 10+3 gradually expand to politics, security, culture and other fields.
21020	XIN_ENG_20070808.0243.LDC2009T13	Under the framework, minister-level meeting system in the diplomatic, financial, economic, agricultural, tourism and labor fields has built up and run healthily.
21021	XIN_ENG_20070808.0243.LDC2009T13	Cooperation in non- traditional security, energy security, education, bird-flu prevention, poverty alleviation and disaster management are all getting on smoothly.
21022	XIN_ENG_20070808.0243.LDC2009T13	At Manila, the ministers urged to draft the 2nd Joint Statement on East Asia Cooperation to round up the accomplishments, because the 10+3 framework compiled in 1999 had not covered with all aspects of cooperation.
21023	XIN_ENG_20070808.0243.LDC2009T13	As another strong signal, the ministers also discussed regional hot issues such as the nuclear issue on the Korean Peninsula.
21024	XIN_ENG_20070808.0243.LDC2009T13	It shows that the 10+3 nations have the common interest in keeping peace and stability in the region and the world.
21025	XIN_ENG_20070808.0243.LDC2009T13	After establishment, 10+3 persist on supporting ASEAN to play an important role in framework like East Asia Summit (EAS), ASEAN Regional Forum (ARF), Asia Cooperation Dialogue (ACD), Asian- Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC), Asia- Europe Meeting (ASEM) and integration of East Asia.
21026	XIN_ENG_20070808.0243.LDC2009T13	However, East Asia, with huge diversities in religions, ideology and culture background, disputes left behind by history and great imbalance in levels of economy and society development, it is still a long way for a final integration.
21027	XIN_ENG_20070808.0243.LDC2009T13	"Economic development in our region is still unbalanced and some countries still lag behind in economic and social development, " Chinese foreign minister Yang Jiechi said to his counterparts in Manila, "The overall competitiveness of East Asia needs to be enhanced."
21028	XIN_ENG_20070808.0243.LDC2009T13	No matter how, the 10+3 has become a win-win road for integration of East Asia, and more important, as leaders stressed in Manila that the 10+3 is one of the most important cooperation frameworks in the region and the main tool in the long-term goal of establishing an East Asian Community.
